# AI Firehose: Cursor context

This is **AI Firehose** (`aigamma/ai-firehose.com` on GitHub), a personal AI-industry intelligence dashboard structured as a daily outlier hunt. It ingests the most salient AI signal each day, organizes it with a non-chat embedding and RAG substrate (Pinecone plus Voyage), and surfaces what is new and breaking out across Day, Week, Month, and Quarter. It is the third in a personal trilogy with aigamma.com (quantitative modeling) and worldthought.com (cited philosophy pages); the RAG substrate is ported from the civil project.

## Authoritative documents (read these first)

Cursor: before answering substantive questions or proposing edits in this repo, ensure you have the context from these files. They are the project's binding conventions; do not infer project structure from filenames alone.

1. **[`CLAUDE.md`](mdc:CLAUDE.md)** is the canonical project guide. It contains:
   - The Writing Rules (em dashes are forbidden in all generative output; never use "RRG" or "Relative Rotation Graph", this project cites Mansfield Relative Performance, 1979; Title Case headings; cite claims).
   - The Core Contracts (idempotency, the rolling-quarter retention, classification without guessing, the AI-grown taxonomy by embedding similarity, determinism in precompute, and the no-chatbot rule). These are non-negotiable for any pipeline or data work.
   - Documentation as Durable Source of Truth, and the Dialectical Absorption Protocol, including the "Sources of Truth and How to Update Them" routing table.
   - The architecture (subsystems: `src/` React frontend, `worker/` Fly ingestion worker and embedding substrate, `netlify/functions/` the one read function, `public/data/` served artifacts, `docs/` tier-2 docs).

2. **[`STEERING_DOCS.md`](mdc:STEERING_DOCS.md)** is the one-page map of the document hierarchy and a "when to read what" cheat sheet.

3. **[`docs/FEATURE_PLAYBOOK.md`](mdc:docs/FEATURE_PLAYBOOK.md)** is the repeatable recipe for onboarding a feature, with a dedicated path for a fully Pinecone/Voyage-integrated one. Read it before adding any feature.

4. **[`LESSONS_LEARNED.md`](mdc:LESSONS_LEARNED.md)** is append-only cumulative wisdom. Read it before any non-trivial change; append to it when you learn something.

Note: `CLAUDE.md` also contains a "Pacing Constraints" section that is Claude-Code-specific (it references Eric's Anthropic billing relationship and parallel-subagent patterns native to Claude Code's harness). That section does not apply to Cursor; read past it.

## The self-improvement rule (non-negotiable for every agent)

When you discover a convention, a failure mode, a better contract, or a process improvement, commit it to the right durable doc before the turn ends, per the routing table in `CLAUDE.md`. Private session memory and chat transcripts decay across sessions; the repository does not. A working tree where the docs lie is a process failure, no different from code that lies.

## Quick start for a new Cursor session

Composer or Agent mode: start any non-trivial task by ensuring `CLAUDE.md` is in context, then read the tier-2 doc for the subsystem you are touching (`docs/INGESTION.md`, `docs/RAG.md`, `docs/SOURCES.md`, `docs/OPERATIONS.md`, `docs/DEPLOYMENT.md`). Every commit that materially changes a subsystem updates that subsystem's tier-2 doc in the same commit.

## Why this file exists

Cursor reads `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files automatically. With `alwaysApply: true`, this rule is injected into Cursor's system prompt for every chat, Composer, or Agent invocation in this repository. The content is intentionally a pointer to `CLAUDE.md` rather than a duplicate, so the canonical conventions live in exactly one place and never drift between Cursor's view and Claude Code's view. The same hub-and-spoke pattern applies to the root `AGENTS.md` (cross-vendor), `.github/copilot-instructions.md` (Copilot), `opencode.md` (OpenCode), and `GEMINI.md` (Antigravity Gemini).
